WEBVTT

00:00:00.332 --> 00:00:02.325
Adam Grant: What's your favorite movie?

00:00:02.349 --> 00:00:04.865
Kid 1: One of them is "Wreck-It Ralph."

00:00:04.889 --> 00:00:06.126
AG: And another?

00:00:06.150 --> 00:00:08.063
Kid 1: "Mr. Peabody and Sherman."

00:00:08.087 --> 00:00:10.291
AG: My kids have seen a lot of cartoons.

00:00:10.315 --> 00:00:11.537
Kids: A lot.

00:00:11.561 --> 00:00:13.355
(Laughter)

00:00:13.379 --> 00:00:15.704
Kid 2: On the TV and in the movie theater.

00:00:15.728 --> 00:00:18.529
AG: My wife and I
love animated films, too.

00:00:18.553 --> 00:00:19.712
When we were growing up,

00:00:19.736 --> 00:00:22.053
there was only one name
in animated movies --

00:00:22.077 --> 00:00:23.838
(Music)

00:00:23.862 --> 00:00:25.012
Disney.

00:00:26.180 --> 00:00:29.681
For about six decades, they were
pretty much the only game in town.